    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give parents rights to be furloughed under the Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme",
        "additional_details": "During the pandemic, many families are trying to juggle working (either from home or otherwise ) and homeschooling with no childcare.\r\n \r\nThis is having a severe impact on mental health of families, particularly on women who often take on the larger load of childcare responsibilities.\r\n",
        "background": "The Government should give parents legal rights to be furloughed under the Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme when they are unable to access childcare, for example where school/nursery is closed. This should be at parent\u2019s discretion, not employers, with protections from losing their jobs.",
